author: Brett Miller
title: Wednesday’s prep volleyball results
text:
Ballard 3, Chief Sealth 1 
Ballard and Chief Sealth traded wins in the first two sets before Ballard shut the door with double-digit victories in the third and fourth sets. Ballard was paced by Ruby Fera, who had 15 kills and 23 digs. Julia Dale added 28 assists and three aces in the victory.
Mount Si 3, Newport 2 
Mount Si pulled out a hard-fought victory in this five-set match in which neither team was able to win two sets in a row. The effort of Patience O’Neal, who had 17 kills, eight aces, and 10 digs, set the tone on the way to an impressive win for the Wildcats. Katie Larson also contributed four aces and 14 digs for Mount Si.
For complete results, visit: http://seattletimes.sportngin.com/schedule/day/league_instance/32008/2015/10/14?subseason=226378&referrer=1855414 .
